WEBVTT

00:03.703 --> 00:05.037
(laughter, chatter)

00:05.039 --> 00:06.481
Hey, guys, why don't
you go upstairs

00:06.482 --> 00:07.814
and wash your hands
before dinner.

00:07.817 --> 00:09.066
(laughter)

00:09.068 --> 00:10.851
I know I only met
you guys at the wedding,

00:10.853 --> 00:12.536
but the amount of times
your name comes up here,

00:12.538 --> 00:14.121
you would think that we
were next-door neighbors.

00:14.123 --> 00:16.290
Well, we practically are now.
Just over the bridge.

00:16.292 --> 00:17.124
Mm-hmm.
Yep.

00:17.126 --> 00:18.492
Don't tell anyone,

00:18.494 --> 00:19.943
but I think
he missed you.

00:19.945 --> 00:22.445
Well, I might've
told some stories

00:22.447 --> 00:23.964
from the old days
now and again.

00:23.966 --> 00:25.549
Aw, do you miss me, buddy?

00:25.551 --> 00:27.384
Yeah, you know I do.

00:27.386 --> 00:29.119
Oh, you should talk.

00:29.121 --> 00:30.420
This one goes on about

00:30.422 --> 00:31.839
his boyhood
BFF so much,

00:31.841 --> 00:33.140
when our kids were little,

00:33.142 --> 00:34.975
they thought Danny Reagan
was the name of a superhero.

00:34.977 --> 00:37.177
It's not?

00:37.179 --> 00:39.847
She's funny.
She's funny.

00:39.849 --> 00:42.649
No, but all jokes aside,
it's... having you guys here,

00:42.651 --> 00:44.651
it's like an early
Christmas present.

00:44.653 --> 00:45.686
Same here.

00:46.571 --> 00:48.071
And it's permanent now?

00:48.073 --> 00:49.573
It's official?

00:49.575 --> 00:50.491
I mean, no more Florida?

00:50.493 --> 00:52.826
Bye-bye, Boca.
Hello, Bay Ridge.

00:52.828 --> 00:54.661
Hello, Bay Ridge.

00:54.663 --> 00:56.330
No, you know,
with my mom being sick,

00:56.332 --> 00:57.447
it was time to come home.

00:57.449 --> 00:59.199
Oh, I'm sorry
to hear about that.

00:59.201 --> 01:00.167
Thanks.

01:00.169 --> 01:01.535
Sit down, relax.

01:01.537 --> 01:02.586
Thank you.

01:02.588 --> 01:03.754
But you know what's nice

01:03.756 --> 01:05.589
is that we'll actually
get to know you guys

01:05.591 --> 01:06.656
after all these years.

01:06.658 --> 01:08.175
Yeah, we should make
something official,

01:08.177 --> 01:09.626
like, uh, once a week,

01:09.628 --> 01:11.628
either dinner or a game
or something.

01:11.630 --> 01:13.680
Done and doner.
All right.

01:13.682 --> 01:14.765
We just hope you're happy here

01:14.767 --> 01:15.883
and you don't miss
Florida too much.

01:15.885 --> 01:18.685
Speaking of missing Florida...

01:18.687 --> 01:21.038
you must've done
pretty well down there

01:21.040 --> 01:22.356
in the Sunshine State,
my friend,

01:22.358 --> 01:24.191
with that, uh,
snazzy Benz you pulled up in.

01:24.193 --> 01:25.692
MICKEY (laughs):
I got lucky.

01:25.694 --> 01:28.678
I wind up in real
estate after college.

01:28.680 --> 01:30.864
Right time,
right place, I guess.

01:30.866 --> 01:32.616
CONNIE: Mickey's being modest.
He works really hard

01:32.618 --> 01:35.202
to give our family
life's little extras.

01:35.204 --> 01:36.519
Um...

01:36.521 --> 01:38.906
Babe, I'm gonna, um,
take the trash cans out, okay?

01:38.908 --> 01:40.374
Danny, we're about to sit.

01:40.376 --> 01:41.942
Yeah, I know. It's, uh...

01:41.944 --> 01:43.710
If I don't do it now,
I'll forget, so...

01:43.712 --> 01:44.962
Yobou obokobay?

01:44.964 --> 01:47.080
Tobotobally.

01:47.082 --> 01:49.032
What on earth was that?

01:49.034 --> 01:51.835
Ob. I never told you about ob?

01:51.837 --> 01:52.669
Ob?

01:52.671 --> 01:54.137
Yeah, it's-it's their

01:54.139 --> 01:55.889
secret language
from fifth grade?

01:55.891 --> 01:57.040
That's right.

01:57.042 --> 01:59.393
Danny made me learn that
before we got engaged.

01:59.395 --> 02:00.644
Oh, brother.

02:00.646 --> 02:01.678
Yeah.

02:01.680 --> 02:03.096
Here, have some more.

02:03.098 --> 02:04.264
We're gonna need it.

