02:14.525 --> 02:16.693
(engine starts)

02:35.746 --> 02:37.514
The perp came running
out of the liquor store

02:37.516 --> 02:38.715
with a bag of cash,

02:38.717 --> 02:42.469
and the clerk right behind him
with a baseball bat.

02:42.471 --> 02:45.355
I yelled, "Police, don't move."

02:45.357 --> 02:47.024
I saw a flash,

02:47.026 --> 02:48.925
and the next thing I know,
I'm lying here.

02:48.927 --> 02:52.529
That flash was a .9 millimeter
in the hand of the wheelman.

02:52.531 --> 02:54.314
I should have seen him coming.

02:54.316 --> 02:56.566
He was around a corner.

02:56.568 --> 02:58.318
When he heard you,
he came out blasting.

02:58.320 --> 03:01.488
There's nothing
you could have done.

03:01.490 --> 03:05.125
The good news is the doctor says
you're going to be just fine.

03:05.127 --> 03:06.960
Yeah, he thinks
I can go home tomorrow.

03:06.962 --> 03:09.246
With a medal pinned
to your chest.

03:12.250 --> 03:13.800
Rest up.

03:13.802 --> 03:15.618
Thank you, Commissioner.

03:18.456 --> 03:21.124
The press is going
to want a few words.

03:21.126 --> 03:22.175
What else is new?

03:22.177 --> 03:23.644
Commissioner.

03:23.646 --> 03:25.562
As you were.

03:25.564 --> 03:26.730
Officer Wallace.

03:26.732 --> 03:27.731
Yes, sir.

03:27.733 --> 03:29.599
Partner's doing fine.

03:29.601 --> 03:30.967
And you both did good work.

03:30.969 --> 03:32.969
Well, we could have
done better, sir.

03:32.971 --> 03:34.571
He came out of a blind spot.

03:34.573 --> 03:35.822
You didn't stand a chance.

03:35.824 --> 03:36.857
That's just it, sir.

03:36.859 --> 03:38.808
That perp never should
have had that gun.

03:38.810 --> 03:42.029
The shooter-- I saw
him casing that shop

03:42.031 --> 03:42.996
four hours earlier.

03:42.998 --> 03:44.531
He kept patting
his hip, you know,

03:44.533 --> 03:46.816
like there was
a gun there...

03:49.003 --> 03:51.204
But you didn't question him.

03:52.423 --> 03:56.843
Because of the new restrictions
on Stop, Question and Frisk?

03:59.497 --> 04:01.548
The judge says we could
get sued personally

04:01.550 --> 04:02.849
if we do a wrong stop.

04:02.851 --> 04:05.168
And you didn't want
to take any chances.

04:06.020 --> 04:08.021
I screwed up, didn't I?

04:09.006 --> 04:10.507
No, son.

04:10.509 --> 04:12.693
We did.

04:20.151 --> 04:21.902
Hey, top of
the morning, Sarge.

04:21.904 --> 04:23.153
There you are.
Follow me.

04:23.155 --> 04:25.522
Little coffee first, boss?
Now.

04:25.524 --> 04:28.125
I got someone who
needs to talk to you.

04:28.127 --> 04:30.026
Okay.

04:30.028 --> 04:32.212
And bah humbug to you, too.

04:33.381 --> 04:36.383
Reagan, this is
Lieutenant Sutton from OCID.

04:37.585 --> 04:39.035
Lieutenant.

04:39.037 --> 04:40.370
Is there a problem?

04:40.372 --> 04:43.039
Well, frankly, that's what
we're here to find out.

04:43.041 --> 04:45.509
This is you,
isn't it, Detective?

04:45.511 --> 04:47.043
Yeah.

04:47.045 --> 04:50.097
That was you taking pictures
at my house?

04:50.099 --> 04:51.064
Yes, it was.

04:51.066 --> 04:52.766
What the hell
is going on here, Sarge?

04:52.768 --> 04:53.900
You got OCID
sitting on my house,

04:53.902 --> 04:55.885
taking pictures
of me and my family?

04:55.887 --> 04:57.687
No, they weren't taking
pictures of you, Danny.

04:57.689 --> 04:59.022
Like hell they weren't.

04:59.024 --> 05:00.407
We weren't on you,
Detective.

05:00.409 --> 05:02.109
We were on your pal,
Michael Patrick.

05:02.111 --> 05:03.443
Mickey?

05:03.445 --> 05:05.996
What... what the hell would
OCID want with Mickey?

05:05.998 --> 05:07.697
Well, maybe because
he's a known member

05:07.699 --> 05:08.832
of the Vasquez Family...

05:08.834 --> 05:10.500
Come on.
...the biggest crime family in Florida.

05:10.502 --> 05:12.369
Right.
And I'm the Lord of the Dance.

05:12.371 --> 05:14.571
I'm not horsing around,
Detective.

05:14.573 --> 05:16.923
Look, it can't be, okay?

05:16.925 --> 05:18.175
It's not even possible.

05:18.177 --> 05:20.761
Last month, the key players
from the top families

05:20.763 --> 05:22.212
across the country
held a summit

05:22.214 --> 05:23.930
masquerading as
a golf outing.

05:23.932 --> 05:25.048
Yeah, right. Okay.

05:25.050 --> 05:26.716
Now, look,
you got the wrong guy.

05:26.718 --> 05:28.718
Okay? Mickey's into real estate.

05:28.720 --> 05:31.438
Want to tell me
what your buddy

05:31.440 --> 05:33.223
in real estate was
doing with them?

05:33.225 --> 05:36.443
There he is, with the rest
of the Vasquez capos.

05:42.099 --> 05:43.700
Mickey's a gangster?

05:45.369 --> 05:46.936
Have a seat, Detective.

05:46.938 --> 05:49.122
We're gonna be
here a while.

